# Expo (NativeWind / Tailwind) — styling rules

- Prefer **Tailwind utilities via `className`** for layout, spacing, typography and colors.
- Use `style={{}}` only when Tailwind is impractical (dynamic numeric values, `Animated`, APIs requiring inline styles, or matching surrounding patterns).
-- Tailwind IntelliSense is configured to use `expo/tailwind.config.js` (see `.vscode/settings.json`).
- When you need programmatic colors (e.g. for `Paper`, icons, `ActivityIndicator`), reuse `expo/theme/colors.ts`.

